caption: So so good
Fresh quality food!
Not good in my opinion.
Excellent food. I had the lobster roll on my 2nd visit. Great sandwich. Filled with lobster. The 1st time I had a shrimp over greens and grains. Excellent as well
Barramundi tacos

First time visit and delightfully surprised by the new england style seafood dishes we ordered. Ordered carryout on a weekday at 5pm. Very prompt. My dinner partner had the lobster roll with truffle tots. Lots of lobster with just the right amount savory, not sweet, dressing. The truffle tots were intermixed with soft shaved parmesan cheese. I ordered the crispy cod and crispy shrimp sandwich. The deep fried protein was delightfully crunchy and fresh tasting. Be forewarned. Nearby street parking is limited.
Always a good meal... fresh seafood and great sides in a casual atmosphere
Really great seafood, I was really impressed!

In this critical area of chicago, every restaurant is perfect. Great food, speedy, friendly and fast.  But, This place is not.  It has great food but the efficiency of the employees is not all that. There are lots of employees but a majority of them are not quick on their feet and they don't work smart to get things up to potential. Service is sloppy and slow.

This is the spot for consistently delicious seafood! Even in Covid times the packaging is great, food stays hot and tasty until consumed. I have ordered from here at least 4 times now and each time has been better than the last! The best part is that it's super affordable for great quality seafood, thank you Brown Bag Seafood Team for keeping my seafood cravings at ease!

Brown Bag Seafood makes what is pretty much a perfect meal for me: catch of the day with greens and a lovely lemon vinaigrette. The Buffalo tots are very tasty and the fried shrimp I occasionally add on are always done perfectly. My only complaint is there isn’t a location closer to home.

The food is consistently good and cooked to perfection.  Without the ability to travel, being able to have fresh seafood any day of the week has been an absolute joy through out the pandemic. We’ve tried a lot of the menu and everything is the best of the best.

5 starred this place the other day and completely forgot to write a review because the aroma from my lobster roll gave me a literal out of body experience. But I'm back now and this place f$@%in' rocks. Great menu items with awesome bases. My buddy got the taco with crispy shrimp. It was so good that it gave him the courage to ask out this girl at the bakery. She inexplicably said no, and we're actually not allowed back in that establishment. That's fine. More time at Brown Bag.
Love this place. I always thought I hated 🐟 but now I get their Daily catch on a salad 3 times a week! Their lemon vinegarette dressing is the best!
Tasty healthy options
Just an excellent spot with great food and a meaningful personal touch.
Food at any Brown Bag is super tasty. My favorite is the crispy cod & shrimp combo. The team working here are the friendliest people! Would definitely recommend Brown Bag & this location!
(Translated by Google) Buffalo everyone!  (Original) Buffalo tots!

changed my mind about white fish! presentation and flavor were all phenomenal and my meal was around ten dollars. my girlfriend’s lobster roll was not as cheap, but while eating it she finally shut up for a bit

Great spot for some affordable seafood! I went for dinner and got a drink and bowl during COVID and enjoyed every bit of it. I might go back for lunch in the future but great spot for sure and will have my business again!

Excellent food, good menu variety and great value.  On my most recent order, there was an issue with Grubhub.  Staff quickly identified the error and recovered immediately, it was exceptional.  I'll be back soon.
Always on point best staff and food always has consistent quality! Frank always rock that grill 👍🏽

This has gone from being one of our top places locally to the very bottom of the list. Their employees are celebrating obnoxiously eg. singing (screaming) loudly and blasting music. I'm all for celebrating, but on a Sunday night and louder than our sound isolating windows can handle. Thanks for the massive headache.
Outstanding Restaurant!  Loved the seafood.  The Ancient Grain Blend and Buffalo Bleu Tots were delish, as well.  Also, environmentally friendly.  Thank you!  HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

Hands down the best lobster roll I have ever had in my life. Brown Bag Seafood offers a plethora of amazing combinations with their protein and bowls while keeping everything at an affordable price. Every time I come, I always have to get the lobster roll. Don't be put off by the price tag, it's well worth it I promise. The lobster knuckles and claws and cooked to perfection with a nice buttery flavor and the english style roll is to die for. If you're on the fence about trying Brown Bag, I highly recommend it as an avid seafood lover.
Reliable healthy food with awesome delivery speed. Yup. Love this place.

I been there three times I love the lobster roll I had the fish and chips and the maui sandwich with extra sauce I didn't like the bread it didnt taste bad it was to much bread I would prefer a pretzel bun next time I'm gonna get lemon wedges and squeeze of the maui next time the fries are so good everything is so fresh.
Quick heathy seafood option that never disappoints!
Love love love the lobster roll and will be back very soon!!
Perfect crispy shrimp! Love the boss sauce!

This place is so delicious. I have wanted to find a place like this for years - simple and healthy and fresh fish and vegetables. The veggie mix is perfect -- kale, Brussels sprouts, broccoli, and green beans. All fresh. Not overly seasoned. They are also always very nice.

super viable food in a value compatible with the reality of the majority of the population. Fresh food, one of the best restaurants in Chicago in the delivered system. Most of the time they don't delay the food ... I LOVE THE SERVICE. I love that you put a table with food right at the entrance for the customer to identify and take your package, sometimes without the need to disturb the waiters.
Never again!!! Didn't receive my complete order, got the runaround for 30mins and not 1 apology.  Edit:Corporate was emailed and rectified the situation quickly.
Service was excellent, food was average.
Long wait time
Brown Bag Seafood Co. is my new favorite go-to for healthy delivery/takeout.  We had the seared tuna (perfectly seasoned and cooked) and salmon (again - perfect, even after traveling for 20min).
Lots of great fish dishes. Super fresh with tons of choices for sauces and sides. Light and airy space looking a tad used but the food is always fabulous!
Always great food, always friendly. Lots of healthy choices, prompt service, and reasonable prices.
Simple healthy food, easy to order, healthy drinks, and lots of daylight to sit inside during the dark winter days. Parking is easy!
Yum! Fresh salmon, so tasty. Tots are so good :)
This place knows how to please their clients. Always with a super nice attitude. The food is reasonably priced, regularly tasty and clean.
We had an awesome time in this restaurant. We enjoyed the amazing vibes and the meals. The staff were super amiable. I am glad we eventually managed to visit here.
Tasty food. Has gluten free options.
Generally only ok. Salad dressing weird, salad greens not cleaned through so some rotten greens.

I've been eating at Brown Bag seafood every chance I get coming into the city. Donna Lee is the owner. She offers, fresh seafood, at affordable prices, along with quick service.  I've been to the one at 3400 Lincoln multiple times, the one across from Maggie Daly park, and the one on Clark Street at the large food Court. If your downtown or around Chicago you have to give this place a try, I was happy when I saw that they now have 13 locations. Donna Lee is an amazing restauranteur. If you love seafood try this place!!!
Great fast casual with healthy options. Friendly staff. Good for kids.
Excellent and fresh food, I liked the ambience this spot has, and the workers were very friendly. Will surely come back again.
Very well organised and convenient restaurant. They serve large meals and for inexpensive rates. I enjoyed the food very much and the staff members were super attentive and chatty. Recommended.
Excellent lobster roll! One huge claw, definitely get it!
It was nice the staff was excellent and food good
Really good here outstanding

I can't wait to go here again! Nutrient dense, hot, quick food. Fresh fish and a hearty serving of vegetables. Crispy garlic bread. Bright, airy interior and they have outdoor seating. Good, solid iced tea.
Customer service was awesome food was great and price was extremely Fair. Lobster roll was amazing shrimp was scrumptious..

Very different format from the usual seafood restaurant. However, the food is made from high quality ingredients and well prepared. Overall very tasty and will have to come back to try some different variations.
Very good food and service was excellenrt!
Have had the shrimp there before, excellent. Had the lobster roll on Thursday, very disappointed, did not taste fresh
Really nice place, very welcoming staff, food is great!
Great Salmon, seared perfectly.. Nice atmosphere & restrooms were clean.
The veggie box with shrimp or salmon was terrific. Very satisfying without the guilt.
Love this place!

Had high expectations.  Cilantro slaw was so so, cauliflower was meh, salmon veggie was good.  Tuna was cooked well, however there was no seasoning on it.  Cod was reminiscent of fish sticks.   Overall a poor experience with the food.  Staff was very patient,  friendly and helpful.
Good, affordable seafood.
Average, nothing to write home about.

Not a true seafood restaurant, more of a seafood style chipotle. Maybe it’s good for those items, but $26 for a lobster roll with a meager portion of poor tasting lobster is not a good value or a fair price.  Gets one additional star for some delicious, well fried tater tots. However, even these were trying too hard with whatever they put on top.
Really good place for seafood! The tuna is amazing, and the shrimp as well, I would definitely recommend. Good location too, and it has an outdoor area if the weather is nice.

Delicious food! Such a great and healthy option. My go to is the salmon green & grains box with extra greens. Very filling and you don’t fill guilty afterwards! The location is also very cute and have outside seating as well. My go to for lunch or dinner!
So so
Delicious and healthy.
Great seafood, good prices.

It's been a few years since we've been in this area of town, and it's always fun to stumble across a new (to us) place to eat. We both had the fish and chips. Very fresh, seasoned fries and the tartar and boss sauces were really good. Kinda out of our price range, but worth it.
Great value for the price. The fish is always delicious even when delivered. My go to place for when I'm short on time and need a quick, healthy, and delicious meal.
Friendly service and delicious food every time! It's such a great feel in the spring/summer when they open the big windoors as well.
I had cod tacos. They were good. Industrial feel atmosphere.  Tater tots were cold but after we complained they gave me hot fresh ones. Nice.

I felt rushed even as I let the one person behind me go ahead and order while I made up my mind. Their menu is meant to be ordered fast but when you are new to a place, it takes a few minutes to get the hang of it.
Great seafood
Nice variety of fish choices with several variations on dishes: tacos, salad, etc
It was nice.
Good prices. Fresh food.
Had to wait forever
Staff needs to keep hygenic environment while switching from register to food processing without gloves. There was single person doing everything. It wasn't too bad but unhygienic.
Fast,friendly, phenomenal food for a good price
Meh.

I recently got food poisoning from their salad and when I called to inform them about the issue they said for any further action to take place I would need a “doctors note”. Poor customer service. Will not be returning.
Very disappointing.  Everything sounded amazing but nothing quite delivered.  The decor is clean, simple and cute.  Paid too much for order at the counter service.
The shrimp tacos are delicious
Very nice
Great food, but the prices...
Great dining experience. Food was delicious. I ordered the salmon and it was cooked perfect and was tasty!
The fish and chips were terrific and my wife thought the grilled shrimp was "perfect".
Best lobster rolls in the city, just wish they were open later
I was very impressed. Large portions. Good portion size . very tasty and fresh. Exceeded my expectations.  Wonderful staff stunning atmosphere

Good quality fast-ish food place for a reasonable price. Restaurant is clean, staff is very friendly. Protein choices are awesome, and they provide so many ways to eat it (power bowl, salad, tacos, etc). Serving sizes are fair, smell and taste great. A pricier lunch than most may want to spend regularly, but a nice occasional treat for tasty, healthy food.
Very good experience!
Spent over a hundred $$ for 4, average tasting lobster rolls. Should be 80 bucks tops here..
I am Uber Eats Driver... They are fast and friendly
Blackened shrimp salad was excellent. Would recommend for a quick bite you can feel good about.
Great food and the place is so beautiful! It is a must during summer, but because the food is so great, give it a try during winter as well.
Excellent fish tacos and very pleasant staff.
Really good seafood and fish.  Great staff. Nice outdoor seating.
Good fried fish sandwiches

Food was delicious and presented in a unique way, in little serving tubs. We got the Salmon veggie box and the Lobster Roll.  The Salmon was okay, what I'd expect of a quick bite place.  But the Lobster Roll was So Good! Would recommend giving it a try, it will cost a bit depending on the market price but worth every bite.  Even comes with a little news paper wrapping in the bottom of the tray.  The overall feel of the restaurant was on point, a fresh seaside dinner.  Really enjoyed the canning jar glasses.  It's the little details that make all the difference.  I'm looking forward to a return visit.
I got the Salmon with the bed of greens. I wasn't expecting much, but it was very good. Great flavor and a solid amount of food. Sort of expensive, but I felt like it was good food for the price.
Yea! Delicious healthy food at a fair price. The salmon vegi box was excellent. We will definitely return.

Great Chicago joint for seafood. I come from England, which has the best fish and chip shops in the world (true, don't argue with me). But this place has the best fish sandwiches I've tasted in the United States since I left my home country. Hint: they don't bread the fish. P. S.: they also deliver.

Overall: Brown bag is a great option for some quality casual seafood lunches or dinners.  The good: The seafood that comes with your combo is right up there with pricey restaurant offerings. They have a daily catch, and our perch was a phenomenal pairing with the power box. It was cooked to perfection, tender, and had a nice griddle to it. There was a nice amount and balance of grains and spinach, and the lemon vinaigrette is a great touch. They also have daily specials for the menu, like free ice cream on Sundays or free delivery on Tuesdays, which is quite the perk.  The not-so-good: The food took quite a bit to come out even though we were one of 2-3 tables on a Sunday late afternoon. The prices are a tad high as well, and the outdoor seating was uncomfortable.  Atmosphere: 9/10 Service: 8/10 Food: 9/10

Hands down the best fish sandwich I’ve ever had. Perfectly prepared. My wife loved her grilled fish over a salad as well. Worth checking out for any seafood lover looking for a quick bite as it’s an order and sit down type place.
Really healthy food prepared nicely.
Good but not great ..quick bite stop... for sure
Great lunch. The shrimp, and Boss sauce was delicious.

I rated 3 stars because the place is very nice yet very pricey for what I got! I ordered the salmon on a bed of greens... tots and a gingeraid..... I paid about $18 and some change. My drink was one size only... i took my food to go because I just wanted to relax at home after work. Now at home I can’t get a refill lol. So maybe bigger cup sizes. For this meal I’d pay $15... yes salmon was great but come on nearly $19 for one person... I’ve visted the downtown location many times and loved it so when I heard of this place closer to home I said ohhhh yeah! Downtown location they’re always nice and refillllsss for my little cup size. I do intend to come back I mean I don’t knock the owner for making a buck or two.

Love the atmosphere. Simple but elegant. Staff were phenomenal, so was the food. We loved the kids menu, so many healthy options. Lots of ways to entertain kids while you wait and eat.   Family friendly for sure. Amazing prices for fresh food and allergen friendly options for GF, soy and dairy.   We will be coming back!
The food was good and the staff was very friendly.

A simple menu but what they make is exceptionally good. I like the simple options of seafood with different bases. I also appreciate that not only do they have a specific kids menu, they also do smaller portions of the adult options.  The clam chowder was quite good and not too heavy. There are some interesting tater tot options that I'd like to try. This is definitely a place I'm going to come back to with the family.
Love this place. Food is great and the staff is even better. We've never had a bad experience here.

Had the fisherman's platter. It was good but it only had one medium piece of fish and 3 medium shrimps along with a small portion of slaw and a decent amount of fries. If it weren't for the fries, I wouldn't have felt sated and I'm not a big eater.
The fish tacos are amazing
Amazing fish tacos

Enjoyed the evening at brown bag ,  very nice environment, great outdoor patio , friendly service and excellent quality food. You can tell they use top notch fresh ingredients and if you like seafood this is a must visit. We had the grilled tacos and dinner plate. Only reason it is not 5 stars is I feel like I was still a bit hungry after the meal but maybe that's just the Midwestern in me expecting too much food.

Good food, friendly staff and kid friendly. Also skinny margarita is totally fine for a rugged manly man. Also how can you not love a place which celebrates taco Tuesday by throwing in 50% more tacos for free!
Food was very good and the service even better.

This place is meh. I had high hopes because the menu looked awesome and the patio is nice. Unfortunately, the grilled fish tacos were under seasoned and really fishy - didn't taste fresh. The lobster roll was nothing special. I will say the tatertots were good.. but overall I won't be back.
Excellent value for a quality. Good place to buy a fish sandwich.  Mr. Meadows knows what I'm talking about.

We got the power box and veggie box, and they were excellent!! Well prepared, fresh and delicious. The curry crab cakes do not disappoint. 😊Also - love the decor, even the restrooms are very tastefully designed.  For parents with little ones - they have the coolest stainless steel changing tables! There are also seats that attach to the table instead of high chairs. These require you to have a foot on the table base to prevent them from toppling over for now. But work well, other than that.  Loved our experience here and will be back often!
Yummy! Will definitely be back here!

Food was good, but a little pricey for what you get. They wouldn't take cash because they had not yet counted the till at 3 in the afternoon so don't forget your card.  Booths have uncomfortable ergonomics, so get a table with the chairs and offer the bench to the friend you came with but don't really like.
